SEC. 3. Article 97 of the same Act is hereby further amended to read as follows:

ГўВЂВњART. 97.

Allowance for good conduct.

ГўВЂВ“ The good conduct of any offender qualified for credit for preventive imprisonment pursuant to Article 29 of this Code, or of any convicted prisoner in any penal institution, rehabilitation or detention center or any other local jail shall entitle him to the following deductions from the period of his sentence:

ГўВЂВњ1. During the first two years of imprisonment, he shall be allowed a deduction of twenty days for each month of good behavior during detention;

ГўВЂВњ2. During the third to the fifth year, inclusive, of his imprisonment, he shall be allowed a reduction of twenty-three days for each month of good behavior during detention;

ГўВЂВњ3. During the following years until the tenth year, inclusive, of his imprisonment, he shall be allowed a deduction of twenty-five days for each month of good behavior during detention;

ГўВЂВњ4. During the eleventh and successive years of his imprisonment, he shall be allowed a deduction of thirty days for each month of good behavior during detention; and
